6:
Wow, so this town is really made up
entirely of ships?!
10:
So what? It's hardly somethin' to get
all riled up about.
14:
Yes it is! I've never even SEEN the
ocean before, you know! It's
massive...
This really is a totally different world!
18:
I want to explore, but I guess we've
got work to do, huh?
22:
Of course. We're here to open some
treasure! This one is for a huge
batch pulled up from the bottom of
the sea.
30:
These are all from thirty years ago,
you say?
32:
That's right. The vessel that sank
was one of ours—our chairman at
the time was actually on board as
well.
33:
We incurred massive losses from
that disaster... But 30 years later, we
seem to have found some of the
wreckage.
37:
The keyhole on this one is
completely covered with rust!
39:
We thought about forcing them
open, but we don't want to damage
whatever was inside.
Do you think you can open them
safely?
44:
Of course I can!
Just leave it to me!
56:
It's so satisfying when they all just
pop open on their own like that!
60:
Okay, that only leaves this one! The
final box.
63:
Hmm... I'm sorry, I don't think I can
open this one.
68:
What's wrong? Does it have a trap
concealed inside it?
71:
No, it's not that... How do I put this...
I just don't want to open this one.
73:
What are you talking about? It's your
job to open these!
77:
It is, but... I don't know how to put
this. It's just... not clicking for me right
now!
81:
What does that even mean?!
Fine, if you won't do it, we'll just break
it open.
83:
This is OUR property. You'd better not
interfere.
89:
Of course, I understand that, but...
Oh gosh, I don't know how to explain!
92:
Oh dear, what seems to be the
problem here?
96: That box... Could you show it to me?
106: I'm sorry! I think I can open it now!
110:
Ring, ring, ring
By the sound of my bell
I bid you open up, little lock!
118:
Ah... you didn't forget our wedding
anniversary after all...
119:
But darling, I've gone and become
an old woman now... so much time
has passed.
125:
A present... from 30 years ago. I'd like
to think that she found closure in
reading her husband's words.
128:
Keyana, how did you know there
was something special about that
box?
134:
To tell you the truth, I didn't actually
know it was special...
135:
I just felt it from the lock, you know?
It was telling me that it did NOT want
to be opened.
136:
It's just like the locks people put on
their own hearts, you know?
141: People also put locks on themselves?
144:
Yeah. You see them from time to
time... People who act mean and
intimidating... They've locked away
their real feelings.
149: And can you open those locks too?
151:
Hmm... I managed to. Once. A long
time ago.
But that was terrifying, so I haven't
done it since!
153:
This power I have... I don't quite get
it. I'm pretty sure it's not magic.
160:
That's right. Someone from the
Academy told me. They also warned
me to stay away from students,
because my power would just cause
confusion!
164: I think it's a very nice power.
166: You made that old lady very happy.
169:
Yeah. You might be right...
Thank you, Stella!
173:
All right, let's get going, everyone!
I've got more locks to pick!
